SonarQube Scanner Installation (Ubuntu - Jenkins Agent)

1. Update the Server

sudo apt update
sudo apt upgrade -y

2. Install Java 17

sudo apt install openjdk-17-jdk -y

Verify Java

java -version

3. Download SonarScanner

cd /opt

sudo wget https://binaries.sonarsource.com/Distribution/sonar-scanner-cli/sonar-scanner-7.3.0.5189-linux-x64.zip

4. Install Unzip

sudo apt install unzip -y

5. Extract SonarScanner

sudo unzip sonar-scanner-7.3.0.5189-linux-x64.zip

6. Rename the Directory

sudo mv sonar-scanner-7.3.0.5189-linux-x64 sonar-scanner

7. Set Ownership

sudo chown -R $USER:$USER /opt/sonar-scanner

8. Add SonarScanner to PATH

echo 'export PATH=$PATH:/opt/sonar-scanner/bin' >> ~/.bashrc

source ~/.bashrc

9. Verify Installation

sonar-scanner --version

Expected Output

SonarScanner CLI 7.x.x
Java 17
Linux

Important Notes

- Install SonarScanner only on the Jenkins Agent (Build Node).
- Do NOT install SonarQube Server on the Jenkins Agent.
- The Jenkins pipeline uses SonarScanner to analyze the source code.
- SonarScanner sends the analysis report to the SonarQube Server running on http://<SonarQube-Server-IP>:9000.
